	+ Cost: $5.50 (AirTrain) + $10.75 (NJ Transit) = $16.25
	+ Travel Time: ~45-60 minutes
	+ Convenience: You'll need to transfer at Newark Penn Station, but it's a relatively seamless process
	+ Pros: More affordable than Amtrak, still a relatively comfortable ride
	+ Cons: Longer travel time, requires a transfer

**Bus:**

* **Newark Liberty International Airport Express Bus:**
	+ Cost: $16 (one-way), $28 (round-trip)
	+ Travel Time: ~45-60 minutes
	+ Convenience: Drops you off at three locations in Manhattan (Grand Central Terminal, Bryant Park, or the Port Authority Bus Terminal)
	+ Pros: Affordable, convenient drop-off locations in Manhattan
	+ Cons: Can be affected by traffic, less comfortable than the train
* **Other Bus Services:**
	+ Cost: Varies by operator (e.g., Greyhound, Megabus), but generally around $10-20
	+ Travel Time: ~45-60 minutes
	+ Convenience: Varies by operator, but often drops you off at the Port Authority Bus Terminal or other locations in Manhattan
	+ Pros: Can be very affordable, frequent departures
