In general, the train is a more convenient and comfortable option, but it can be more expensive. The bus is a more affordable option, but it may take longer and be less comfortable. If you prioritize convenience and speed, the train might be the better choice. If you're on a tighter budget and don't mind a potentially longer journey, the bus could be the way to go.

Keep in mind that prices and travel times may vary depending on the time of day, traffic, and other factors, so be sure to check the schedules and prices in advance to plan your trip accordingly.
